Advanced reconcile input with account ID

This is the most reliable for reconcile because the CyberArk reconcile API requires the account ID.

cyberark_accounts:
  - name: was
    username: "{{ was_user }}"
    safe: "APP_SAFE"
    account_id: "12_34"
    password_fact: "was_password"

  - name: mq
    username: "{{ mq_user }}"
    safe: "MQ_SAFE"
    account_id: "56_78"
    password_fact: "mq_password"
Idempotency note

Retrieve mode is fully idempotent: it only reads from CyberArk and uses changed_when: false.

Reconcile is an action in CyberArk. This role prevents duplicate reconcile submission while PasswordChangeInProcess is already true. After CyberArk finishes, another mode: reconcile run is a new reconcile request by definition, so it will submit again unless you control it with your workflow or provide a change/request gate. CyberArk’s reconcile endpoint marks an account for automatic reconciliation by CPM, so repeated calls are repeated management actions.
